OL,3,CRecycling plant fined after exposing
OL,4,Cworkers to cancer-causing dust
OL,6,FEsken Renewables Limited, who operated
OL,7,Fthe site at Port Clarence Road,
OL,8,Fpleaded guilty of breaching Regulation
OL,9,F7(1) of the Control of Substances
OL,10,FHazardous to Health (COSHH)
OL,11,FRegulations 2002 and were fined
OL,12,F#160,000 and ordered to pay #5,310.35
OL,13,Fin costs at Teesside Magistrates'
OL,14,FCourt on 23 May.
OL,16,FSpeaking after the hearing, HSE
OL,17,Finspector Matthew Dundas said: "The
OL,18,Fexpected standard is to control
OL,19,Fexposure to as low a level as is
OL,20,Freasonably practicable.
